name: Gepard
descHash: A captain in the Silvermane Guards and an outstanding warrior of Belobog. He is meticulous and vigilant to the core and is always true to himself.

29328.name: Credit
29328.desc: This currency, used by the Interastral Peace Corporation to settle accounts with its customers, is now widely accepted as the hard currency for space travel.
29328.lore: "People run around fighting and trading for numbers in a terminal, but the truly precious cannot be bought."

67219.name: Horn of Snow
67219.desc: Broken horn of a Frigid Prowler. Can be used for the Ascension of Ice characters.
67219.lore:
The Silvermane Guards would host contests where the winner must take a body part from a monster and bring it back within a set time limit. This cold broken horn must have been a trophy of one such contest.

"Sir Bova, this is no moose horn and is certainly not fit for decoration above the Geomarrow furnace."

125435.name: Tracks of Destiny
125435.lore: Your victory is secured by countless failures, and the small steps you have taken led you to the turning point of fate.

270195.name: Guardian's Lament
270195.lore:
Together with this visor, the twisted wish of a Guardian also lies broken.
She had wanted to find a way out for her people to escape the Everwinter, but ended up becoming a puppet of a consciousness beyond her.

"Supreme Guardian, the title passed down to generations of Belobog's rulers, the one who looked after all the people — It never occurred to anyone that the Guardians themselves also long for care and protection."

409960.name: Traveler's Guide
409960.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>20,000</nobr> Character EXP.
409960.lore:
Required reading for world exploration. Press the "Read" button to tune in to an attractive voice in a language you understand, telling you about the legendary encounters of renowned adventurers across different worlds as well as the precious wisdom and knowledge that they have gathered.

"All-new series of the Traveler's Guide, The Chef's Manual to Galactic Cuisine, is now available for purchase."
"For submissions, please connect to synesthesia beacon ERD-23θ to contact an Intelligentsia Guild representative. Method of payment can be arranged to your convenience."

409961.name: Adventure Log
409961.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>5000</nobr> Character EXP.
409961.lore:
A neatly organized collection of educational adventure notes containing countless illustrations and texts entailing adventures from beginning to end, as well as valuable information and survival-related techniques.

"Why not just digitize it and save it on a photolith disk? That'd be much more convenient."
"Advanced technology is far more fragile than you'd think when faced with stellar storms and neuron flow eruptions. Besides, I'm sure the author of this book wanted people to read it in the simplest of ways."

409962.name: Travel Encounters
409962.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>1000</nobr> Character EXP.
409962.lore:
A travel diary with messy handwriting and random content. It's not of much use to you.

"Dan Heng, hurry up and finish reading it so you can throw it away."

549407.name: Silvermane Badge
549407.desc: Pin badge worn by soldiers of the Silvermane Guards. Crude material used for enhancement.
549407.lore:
It is full of scratches from the erosion of wind and snow.

"In ancient times, there was only one way Silvermane Guards could retire: death."
comeFrom: Outlying Snow Plains: Silvermane Guards or other enemies
Corridor of Fading Echoes: Everwinter Shadewalkers or other enemies

633348.name: Silvermane Insignia
633348.desc: Military rank insignia worn by captains of the Silvermane Guard. Normal material used for enhancement.
633348.lore:
Maybe it's a proof of heroics that you can brag about to your family. Maybe it's a lucky charm that protects you from a bullet.

"Times have changed."
comeFrom: Outlying Snow Plains: Equilibrium Level 2+ Silvermane Guards or other enemies
Corridor of Fading Echoes: Equilibrium Level 2+ Everwinter Shadewalkers or other enemies

635668.name: Endurance of Bronze
635668.desc: A crude but durable ancient hand-held bronze shield. Used to level up Traces slightly for Preservation characters.
635668.lore:
Ancient legends entail a war where humans exhausted all primitive methods, following the gods into battle against overwhelmingly powerful beasts.
This shield is a witness to that war.

"There's no choice but to stop it, even if the efforts are futile."

717289.name: Silvermane Medal
717289.desc: Medal of honor worn by soldiers of the Silvermane Guards with gallant and meritorious service. Advanced material used for enhancement.
717289.lore:
A proof of honor awarded to those that fought against Fragmentum creatures, Underworlders, and sudden disasters.
It is not usually pinned onto the recipient's chest, but rather placed onto his coffin.

"Remember, young Gepard. It is not a toy: it is the destiny and blood of the Landau family."
comeFrom: Outlying Snow Plains: Equilibrium Level 4+ Silvermane Guards or other enemies
Corridor of Fading Echoes: Equilibrium Level 4+ Everwinter Shadewalkers or other enemies

836254.name: Safeguard of Amber
836254.desc: An unusual shield embedded with ambers mined from beyond the skies. Used to level up Traces significantly for Preservation characters.
836254.lore:
The wielder of this shield is seemingly protected by an invisible shield wall, immune to fiery arrows or mountainous claws.
Ancient legends entail a war where a tribal hero wielding a bronze shield charged to their death against a Leviathan, together with warriors armed with fiery spears.
This shield is a witness to that war.

"Do not cross the line."

920195.name: Oath of Steel
920195.desc: A shield forged with irreplaceable craftsmanship from an unknown alloy. Used to level up Traces moderately for Preservation characters.
920195.lore:
It may be a large shield, but it feels as light as a feather. Even after taking on a full charge, no marks can be seen on the face of the shield.
Ancient legends tell of a war where high-spirited warriors wielded deathray-beaming spears and shields forged of Frost Steel, defended a nation destined to falter in the face of war.
This shield is a witness to that war.

"Powerful voices chant: 'The enemies are at our gates!'"

ranks.name: Due Diligence
ranks.descHash: When using Skill, increases the base chance to Freeze enemies by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>.

ranks.name: Lingering Cold
ranks.descHash: After an enemy Frozen by Skill is unfrozen, their SPD is reduced by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> for <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> turn(s).

ranks.name: Never Surrender
ranks.descHash:
Ultimate Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Talent Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.

ranks.name: Faith Moves Mountains
ranks.descHash: When Gepard is in battle, all allies' Effect RES increases by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr>.

ranks.name: Cold Iron Fist
ranks.descHash:
Skill Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Basic ATK Lv. +1, up to a maximum of Lv. 10.

ranks.name: Unyielding Resolve
ranks.descHash: When his Talent is triggered, Gepard's action is Advanced Forward by <nobr>100%</nobr>, and he restores extra HP equal to <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> of his Max HP.

skills.name: Fist of Conviction
skills.descHash: Deals Ice DMG equal to #1[i]% of Gepard's ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Daunting Smite
skills.descHash:
Deals Ice DMG equal to #1[i]% of Gepard's ATK to a single enemy, with a #2[i]% base chance to Freeze the enemy for #3[i] turn(s).
While Frozen, the enemy cannot take action and will take Additional Ice DMG equal to #4[i]% of Gepard's ATK at the beginning of each turn.

skills.name: Enduring Bulwark
skills.descHash: Applies a Shield to all allies, absorbing DMG equal to #1[i]% of Gepard's DEF plus #3[i] for #2[i] turn(s).

skills.name: Unyielding Will
skills.descHash: When struck with a killing blow, instead of becoming knocked down, Gepard's HP immediately restores to #1[i]% of his Max HP. This effect can only trigger once per battle.

skills.name: Attack
skills.descHash: Attack an enemy, and when the battle starts, reduce their Toughness of the corresponding Type.

skills.name: Comradery
skills.descHash: After Gepard uses his Technique, when the next battle begins, a Shield will be applied to all allies, absorbing DMG equal to <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> of Gepard's DEF plus <nobr>#3[i]</nobr> for <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> turn(s).

embedBonusSkill.name: Fighting Spirit
embedBonusSkill.descHash: Gepard's ATK increases by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> of his current DEF. This effect will refresh at the start of each turn.

embedBonusSkill.name: Integrity
embedBonusSkill.descHash: Gepard has a higher chance to be attacked by enemies.

embedBonusSkill.name: Commander
embedBonusSkill.descHash: When "Unyielding Will" is triggered, Gepard's Energy will be restored to <nobr>100%</nobr>.

voiceItems.title: First Meeting
voiceItems.text: My name is Gepard Landau, I'm a captain of the Silvermane Guards. If you discover anything suspicious in the city, you can always report it to me.

voiceItems.title: Greeting
voiceItems.text: You're here. I just finished training.

voiceItems.title: Parting
voiceItems.text: My apologies, I still have an assignment to attend to. I'll have to see you off from here.

voiceItems.title: About Self
voiceItems.text: As a Silvermane Guard, I observe the oath not because I fear to go against it, but because I am obliged to uphold it.

voiceItems.title: Chat: Belobog
voiceItems.text: Belobog is far from buried in the snow curtain. This city is the planet's last bastion against the ferocity of the Eternal Freeze.

voiceItems.title: Hobbies
voiceItems.text: I grow flowers, *sigh* ...It's just that I'm not very good at it.

voiceItems.title: Annoyances
voiceItems.text: My sister's songs are very popular among the Guards — there's always someone singing one when we're off duty. Recently I've found myself humming them without realizing, even when I'm on duty... *sigh*

voiceItems.title: Something to Share
voiceItems.text: The Landau family has had the honor and responsibility of serving the supreme guardians for generations. Only by becoming a shield for the people is one worthy of the title "Architect."

voiceItems.title: Knowledge
voiceItems.text: Lately, many children have come to ask me how to become a captain... *sigh* To be honest, the best advice I can give is to keep training and have a balanced diet.

voiceItems.title: About Bronya
voiceItems.text: Lady Bronya has ventured deep into the most dangerous regions of the front line with us — many times for that matter.

voiceItems.title: About Serval
voiceItems.text: Many people seem to like talking about how my sister changed since she left the Guards, but in reality... she's exactly the same person.

voiceItems.title: About Pela
voiceItems.text: I heard my sister started asking Pela to look after my flowers when I'm away... I hope it's not too much trouble for her.

voiceItems.title: About Cocolia
voiceItems.text: I've always firmly believed that no one knows this city better or loves it more than the supreme guardian.

voiceItems.title: About Sampo
voiceItems.text: He's very... cunning. According to leads provided by citizens, he's got his hands on a number of ancient relics. He sold off most of them, but it seems he's using others to commit various frauds.

storyItems.title: Character Details
storyItems.text:
The honorable and upstanding captain of the Silvermane Guards who bears the noble Landau family name.
In the frost-whipped city of Belobog, life can still go on in normality...
This is in no small part thanks to Gepard and his Silvermane Guards who protect the peace of everyday life.
